{'contentformat': 'text/x-wiki', 'contentmodel': 'wikitext', '*': '{{PokémonPrevNext/Head|type=Fire}}\n{{PokémonPrevNext/GO|species=Flareon}}\n{{PokémonPrevNext/Pokémon|type=Fire|prevnum=135|prev=Jolteon|nextnum=137|next=Porygon|round=none}}\n{{PokémonPrevNext/Disambig|species=Flareon}}\n|}\n{{Pokémon Infobox\n|name=Flareon\n|jname=ブースター\n|jtranslit=Būsutā\n|tmname=Booster\n|ndex=136\n|oldjdex=183\n|jdex=187\n|sdex=166\n|u2dex=094\n|karea=Coastal\n|kdex=080\n|adex=126\n|fbrow=184\n|abrow=100\n|obrow=078\n|opbrow=057\n|typebox=1\n|type1=Fire\n|category=Flame\n|height-ftin=2\'11"\n|height-m=0.9\n|weight-lbs=55.1\n|weight-kg=25.0\n|abilityn=d\n|ability1=Flash Fire\n|abilityd=Guts\n|egggroupn=1\n|egggroup1=Field\n|eggcycles=35\n|evtotal=2\n|evat=2\n|expyield=184\n|oldexp=198\n|lv100exp=1,000,000\n|gendercode=31\n|color=Red\n|catchrate=45\n|body=08\n|pokefordex=flareon\n|generation=1\n|friendship=70\n}}\n\'\'\'Flareon\'\'\' ([[List of Japanese Pokémon names|Japanese]]: \'\'\'ブースター\'\'\' \'\'Booster\'\') is a {{type|Fire}} {{OBP|Pokémon|species}} introduced in [[Generation I]].\n\nIt [[Evolution|evolves]] from {{p|Eevee}} when exposed to a [[Fire Stone]]. It is one of Eevee\'s [[Eeveelution|final forms]], the others being {{p|Vaporeon}}, {{p|Jolteon}}, {{p|Espeon}}, {{p|Umbreon}}, {{p|Leafeon}}, {{p|Glaceon}}, and {{p|Sylveon}}.\n\n==Biology==\nFlareon is a mammalian, quadruped Pokémon covered in short, reddish-orange fur. It has long ears with black interiors, dark eyes, and a small black nose. There are three small toes and a yellow paw pad on each foot. Fluffy yellow fur forms a small tuft on its head, as well as its bushy tail and a mane around its chest and neck. It will fluff out its collar to cool down its high body temperature. This high temperature is caused by its internal flame sac. Flareon stores and heats inhaled air in this sac, and then exhales it as fire. It is an {{wp|omnivore}} that roasts either {{Berries}} or prey before consumption. Flareon is mostly found in {{DL|List of Pokémon by habitat|Urban Pokémon|populated areas}} and is rarely seen in the wilderness.\n\n==In the anime==\n[[File:Virgil Flareon.png|thumb|250px|left|Flareon in the {{pkmn|anime}}]]\n===Major appearances===\nFlareon debuted in \'\'[[EP040|The Battling Eevee Brothers]]\'\', under the ownership of {{DL|Eevee brothers|Pyro}}. It was targeted in one of {{TRT}}\'s schemes.\n\nA Flareon appeared in \'\'[[EP056|The Ultimate Test]]\'\', where {{Ash}} battled it during the [[Pokémon League]] entrance exam.\n\nA Flareon appeared in \'\'[[EP183|Trouble\'s Brewing]]\'\' and \'\'[[EP226|Espeon, Not Included]]\'\', under the ownership of Koume, one of the [[Kimono Girl|Kimono Sisters]]. It was seen when Team Rocket disrupted the Kimono Sisters\' tea ceremony.\n\nA Flareon appeared in \'\'[[EP240|Some Like it Hot]]\'\', under the ownership of [[Egan]]. It was used in Egan\'s pursuit to {{pkmn2|caught|catch}} a {{p|Magcargo}}. Flareon was initially unsuccessful, but after Egan applied {{an|Misty}}\'s strategies, it was able to defeat a {{pkmn2|giant}} Magcargo that Egan caught\n\nA Flareon debuted in \'\'[[AG077|A Fan with a Plan]]\'\', under the ownership of [[Savannah]]. It was used in the first round of the [[Rubello Town]] [[Pokémon Contest]] in \'\'[[AG078|Cruisin\' for a Losin\']]\'\'.\n\nA Flareon appeared in \'\'[[DP174|Last Call — First Round!]]\'\', under the ownership of [[Ursula]]. It evolved from {{p|Eevee}} during the [[Appeal|Performance Stage]] of the [[Sinnoh Grand Festival]]. It reappeared in \'\'[[DP175|Opposites Interact!]]\'\', where it was used along with {{TP|Ursula|Gabite}} in a [[Double Battle|two-on-two]] [[Contest Battle]] against {{an|Dawn}}; it went up against {{TP|Dawn|Pachirisu}} and {{TP|Dawn|Mamoswine}}.\n\nA male Flareon debuted in \'\'[[BW102|Team Eevee and the Pokémon Rescue Squad!]]\'\', along with an Eevee and her other evolutions at the time, under the ownership of [[Virgil]]. He reappeared in a flashback in [[BW103|the next episode]]. Flareon physically reappeared in \'\'[[BW108|A Unova League Evolution!]]\'\', where he battled [[Cameron\'s Lucario]] during the semifinals of the [[Vertress Conference]], and ultimately won.\n\nA Flareon appeared in \'\'[[BW135|Mystery on a Deserted Island!]]\'\', where it evolved from one of three {{p|Eevee}} with a [[Fire Stone]] found on the {{OBP|Deserted Island|BW135}}.\n\nA Flareon appeared in \'\'[[PK25|Eevee & Friends]]\'\' with an {{p|Eevee}} and its other evolutions, including the newly introduced {{p|Sylveon}}. It has a shy personality and tends to raise the temperature considerably as a defense mechanism.\n\nA {{pkmn2|wild}} Flareon appeared in \'\'[[SM065|Turning Heads and Training Hard!]]\'\', where it was summoned to help [[Ilima]]\'s Eevee perform {{m|Extreme Evoboost}}. It reappeared in the [[Poké Problem]] segment of the [[SM066|next episode]], where it saw Ilima and Eevee off.\n\n===Minor appearances===\nA {{pkmn|Trainer}}\'s Flareon appeared in \'\'[[EP073|Bad to the Bone]]\'\'.\n\nA Flareon appeared in \'\'[[EP086|Pikachu Re-Volts]]\'\', where it was among the Pokémon controlled by [[Cassidy]] and [[Butch]] at [[Mandarin Island North]], alongside a {{p|Vaporeon}} and {{p|Jolteon}}.\n\nA Flareon appeared in the Japanese credits of \'\'[[PK04|Pikachu\'s Rescue Adventure]]\'\'.\n\nA Flareon appeared in \'\'[[EP122|Flower Power]]\'\' as a part of [[Florando]]\'s annual [[Pokémon Exhibition]].\n\nA Flareon appeared in [[Evolution|Gary\'s demonstration]] in \'\'[[EP272|Johto Photo Finish]]\'\', where it evolved from an {{p|Eevee}}.\n\nA Flareon appeared in [[Evolution|Brock\'s demonstration]] in \'\'[[AG011|A Bite to Remember]]\'\', where it evolved from an {{p|Eevee}}.\n\nA Flareon made a brief cameo appearance in the opening sequence of \'\'[[M11|Giratina and the Sky Warrior]]\'\' together with an {{p|Eevee}} and its six other evolutions at the time.\n\nA Flareon appeared in \'\'[[DP123|Old Rivals, New Tricks!]]\'\', under the ownership of a [[Pokémon Coordinator]] competing in the [[Sandalstraw Town]] [[Pokémon Contest]].\n\nA {{pkmn|Performer}}\'s Flareon appeared in a video in \'\'[[XY080|Performing with Fiery Charm!]]\'\'.\n\nA Flareon appeared in a fantasy in \'\'[[XY090|Tag Team Battle Inspiration!]]\'\', where {{an|Shauna}} imagined what [[Serena\'s Eevee]] could evolve into.\n\nA Flareon appeared in \'\'[[XY095|Love Strikes! Eevee, Yikes!]]\'\', where a {{pkmn2|wild}} {{p|Quilladin}} tried to win its affections. However, it wasn\'t impressed by it efforts and attacked it with {{m|Flamethrower}} before walking off.\n\nA Trainer\'s Flareon appeared in \'\'[[M20|I Choose You!]]\'\'.\n\nA Trainer\'s Flareon appeared in \'\'[[SM034|A Crowning Moment of Truth!]]\'\', where it was seen receiving the Wela Crown during the [[Wela Fire Festival\u200e]].\n\n===Pokédex entries===\n{{Animedexheader|Hoenn}}\n{{Animedexbody|AG077|Flareon|May\'s Pokédex|Flareon, the Flame Pokémon. Flareon is the evolved form of {{p|Eevee}}. The air it inhales is ignited by a flame inside its body and expelled as fire.}}\n{{Animedexfooter/Pokémon|\'\'Advanced Generation\'\'|Hoenn}}\n{{Animedexheader|Sinnoh}}\n{{Animedexbody|DP174|Flareon|Dawn\'s Pokédex|Flareon, the Flame Pokémon, and an evolved form of Eevee. It stores some of the air it breathes in its internal flame sac, which heats its body to over three thousand degrees.}}\n{{Animedexfooter/Pokémon|\'\'Diamond & Pearl\'\'|Sinnoh}}\n{{Animedexheader|Unova}}\n{{Animedexbody|BW102|Flareon|Ash\'s Pokédex|Flareon, the Flame Pokémon. Flareon\'s internal flame ignites its breath, which is exhaled as fire.}}\n{{Animedexfooter/Pokémon|\'\'Best Wishes\'\'|Unova}}\n\n==In the manga==\n[[File:Pyro Flareon EToP.png|thumb|200px|Flareon in [[The Electric Tale of Pikachu]]]]\n===In The Electric Tale of Pikachu manga===\nA Flareon belonging to [[Eevee brothers|Pyro]] appeared in \'\'[[ET06|To Evolve or Not to Evolve, That Is the Question!]]\'\', where it battled {{OBP|Ash\'s Pikachu|EToP}}, but was easily defeated.\n\n====Pokédex entries====\n{{Mangadexheader}}\n{{Mangadexbody|The Electric Tale of Pikachu|[[ET06]]|Evolved with the Fire Stone. Its body contains flame glands.}}\n{{Mangadexfooter}}\n\n===In the Magical Pokémon Journey manga===\nA Flareon appeared in \'\'[[PPP01|How Do You Do, Pikachu?]]\'\'.\n\n===In the Pokémon Adventures manga===\n{{main|Vee}}\nIn \'\'[[PS019|Blame it on Eevee]]\'\', a mutated Eevee could switch between his evolved forms, one of which is a Flareon. {{adv|Red}} {{pkmn2|caught}} him, added him to his [[Party|team]], and [[nickname]]d him Vee. Later, it used the [[Evolutionary stone|Fire, Water, and Thunder stones]] of [[Vermilion City|Vermilion Harbor]], which were given to him by {{adv|Giovanni}}, to evolve and [[Devolution|devolve]] him freely and faster. Eventually, he lost the ability to devolve after permanently becoming an {{p|Espeon}}, but Red felt more content now that he\'d been freed from the pain that [[Team Rocket]]\'s experiments had dealt.\n\nA Flareon appeared in \'\'[[PS058|The Kindest Tentacruel]]\'\' as one of the Pokémon in {{adv|Yellow}}\'s fantasy about evolution via evolutionary stone.\n\nA Flareon caught by {{adv|Crystal}} and lent to {{adv|Emerald}} for his [[Battle Pike]] challenge appeared in \'\'[[PS309|Moving Past Milotic]]\'\'.\n\nA Flareon appeared in \'\'[[PS448|Pleased as Punch With Parasect]]\'\', under the ownership of a [[Kimono Girl]].\n\nA Flareon appeared in a fantasy in the {{chap|X & Y}}.\n\n==In the TCG==\n{{main|Flareon (TCG)}}\n\n==Other appearances==\n===\'\'{{mov|Detective Pikachu}}\'\'===\nA Flareon briefly appeared in \'\'{{mov|Detective Pikachu}}\'\', under the ownership of [[Howard Clifford]]. It evolved from his {{p|Eevee}}.\n\n==Game data==\n===Pokédex entries===\n{{Dex/Header|type=fire}}\n{{Dex/Gen/1|gen=I|reg1=Kanto|num1=136}}\n{{Dex/Entry2|v=Red|v2=Blue|t2=FFF|entry=When storing thermal energy in its body, its temperature could soar to over {{tt|1600 degre